ool of Technology Admission Requirements \\nLeavitt School of Health Admission Requirements \\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\nComputer Requirements \\nNo Standardized Testing \\nHealth and Nursing Clinical Information \\nStudent Teaching Information \\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\nFAQs about Transferring \\nTransfer to WGU \\nTransferrable Certifications \\nRequest WGU Transcripts \\nInternational Transfer Credit \\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n866.225.5948\\n\\n\\n\\n\\nApply Now\\nRequest Info\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\nInformation Technology\\n\\n\\nCybersecurity\\nCloud\\nManagement\\nData Analytics\\nDevelopment\\nCertifications\\nTrends\\nCareer\\nThought Leadership\\nArtificial Intelligence\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\nSubscribe to the WGU Blog\\nStay up-to-date on the latest articles, tips, and insights from the team at WGU.\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\nMORE ARTICLES\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n6 Qualifications Needed to Become a Software Engineer\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\nInformation Technology\\n\\n\\nCareer\\n\\n\\n See More Tags \\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n      By\\n      \\n        Linsi Tuttle, Senior Copywriter\\n\\n\\n      Reviewed by\\n      \\n        Jared Plumb, Associate Dean and Director, School of Technology\\n\\nFeb 3, 2025\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\nSoftware engineers bring computer systems to life. These IT professionals design, develop, and deploy everything from desktop applications and cybersecurity tools to video games and operating systems. By leveraging modern programming languages, mathematics, and computer science principles, they construct efficient, reliable software programs. Software engineers collaborate with other specialists, including system architects, database administrators, and project managers, to identify problems and develop comprehensive solutions.\\xa0\\nIf you’re interested in a career in software engineering, it’s important to understand the specific skills and educational requirements necessary for success in this field. Keep reading to discover six essential qualifications that will help you excel as a software engineer and learn how to take the first steps toward this exciting career path.\\n1. Bachelor's Degree in Software Engineering\\xa0\\nWhile many software engineers are self-taught, a bachelor's degree in software engineering provides a significant competitive advantage. Employers often prefer to hire candidates who hold at least a bachelor's degree because they are likely to have the skills needed to build complex systems. A bachelor's degree in computer science, software engineering, or a related field can provide developers with extensive programming knowledge, teaching them the principles of computer science and how to apply them to real-world challenges. Earning a degree also offers an opportunity to develop proficiency in specialized areas such as network administration, software security, and user interface design. A bachelor's degree is typically a minimum requirement for high-paying roles such as senior developer or team lead positions.\\xa0\\xa0\\n2. Software Engineering Skills\\xa0\\xa0\\nA software engineer needs a balance of both technical knowledge and nontechnical abilities to thrive in this dynamic field. Some of the most important skills include:\\xa0 \\xa0\\n\\nProficiency in programming languages such as JavaScript, Linux/Unix, HTML, CSS, C#, C++, Java, Ruby, PHP, Python, and SQL\\nExperience working with source code and version repository\\nFamiliarity with UI Toolkits and frameworks\\nAbility to transform requirements into design concepts and entity relationship diagrams (ERDs)\\nData analysis\\nAbility to write precise, detailed technical documentation\\nExperience with software engineering best practices\\nWritten and verbal communication\\nCollaboration\\nProblem-solving\\nOrganization\\nTime management\\nProject management\\nKnowledge of the latest industry trends\\nAttention to detail\\nAdaptability\\xa0\\n\\n3. Internship\\nInternships allow burgeoning software engineers to gain experience, expand their skill set, and familiarize themselves with workplace culture and etiquette. During an internship, professionals work on various projects under the supervision and guidance of more experienced employees. Internship positions are valuable networking opportunities, allowing new software engineers to build professional relationships and discover job opportunities. The hands-on experience gained through an internship also allows participants to add work samples to their portfolios. By showcasing their past work in a portfolio, engineers can increase their employability and stand out in an increasingly competitive job market.\\xa0\\xa0\\n4. Entry-level Experience\\xa0\\nEntry-level experience for software engineers usually involves working on small projects or specific components of larger projects. Whether these engineers are building user interfaces, debugging code, or adding new functionalities, the work of entry-level software engineers directly contributes to the organizational objectives. An essential aspect of a beginner software engineering role is collaborating with other IT professionals and business stakeholders. This provides new engineers an opportunity to hone soft skills like professional communication, emotional intelligence, and problem-solving. In an entry-level role, software engineers also gain a strong understanding of computer science basics such as data structures, algorithms, system design, and database management systems.\\xa0\\nIndividuals with a bachelor’s degree in software engineering, computer science, or a related field often start out in the following roles:\\xa0\\n\\nApplications Developer\\xa0\\nGame Developer\\xa0\\nMultimedia Programmer\\xa0\\xa0\\nWeb Developer\\nWeb Designer\\xa0\\xa0\\nSoftware Engineer\\xa0\\nComputer Programmer\\nQuality Assurance Tester\\nFront-end Developer\\nBack-end Developer\\nProgrammer Analyst\\n\\n\\xa0After gaining some experience in the software engineering field, professionals may also qualify for roles such as:\\n\\nInformation Systems Manager\\nSenior Software Engineer\\nLead Developer\\nIT Consultant\\nCybersecurity Analyst\\nEngineering Manager\\n\\n5. Certifications\\nProfessional certifications demonstrate a software engineer’s dedication and expertise to potential clients and employers, providing a substantial advantage over other job applicants. Because software engineering is a fast-growing field, certifications also play an increasingly important role in ensuring that professionals keep up with industry changes. Some of the most useful certifications for software engineers are Amazon Web Services (AWS) Certified Developer, Microsoft Certified Solutions Developer (MCSD), Oracle Certified Java Programmer (OCJP), and Cisco Certified Network Associate (CCNA).\\xa0\\nCoding boot camps offer another avenue for building skills in programming, web development, and computer science. These camps offer immersive, fast-paced training as well as the opportunity to connect with industry leaders in the technology field.\\xa0\\n6. Master's Degree in Software Engineering or a Similar Field\\xa0\\nA master's degree can equip individuals with advanced skills in specific domains such as cybersecurity and information assurance, data analytics, and information technology management. Master’s degrees expand on students' existing knowledge, challenging them to learn innovative strategies and take on more complex software engineering projects. By earning a master’s degree, a software engineer can enhance their job prospects and qualify for specialized or senior-level roles, including those in machine learning, artificial intelligence, video game design, and data science. Additional education beyond a bachelor’s degree can also empower professionals to negotiate higher salaries in their current positions.\\nBecoming a Software Engineer\\xa0\\nThe technology field is booming. According to the U.S. Bureau of Labor Statistics (BLS), the employment of both software developers and computer and information systems managers is projected to grow by 17% from 2023 to 2033. This is notably faster than the growth rate for all occupations, making now an ideal time to enter or advance within the software engineering industry.\\xa0\\nIf you’re ready to take the next step toward a lucrative, exciting software engineering career, consider earning a degree from WGU. Our degree programs are designed with input from industry experts and cover the latest technologies, methods, and trends. WGU’s Bachelor of Science in Software Engineering degree program provides a strong educational foundation in scripting and programming, web development, mobile application development, user experience design, software quality assurance, and other essential subjects. The curriculum also includes the AWS Certified Cloud Practitioner, CompTIA Project+, and ITIL® Foundation certifications at no additional cost.\\xa0\\nWGU’s competency-based education model allows students to progress as quickly as they demonstrate mastery of course material, meaning that you can potentially save time and money by graduating faster. We also offer low, flat-rate tuition and personalized, one-on-one faculty support for each student. Embark on your academic journey by applying today.\\xa0\\xa0\\xa0\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\nReady to Start Your Journey?\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\nBUSINESS\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\nBachelor's Degrees\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\nMaster's Degrees\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\nSee All Degrees\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\nTEACHING\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\nBachelor's Degrees\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\nMaster's Degrees\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\nState Licensure Information\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\nIT\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\nBachelor's Degrees\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\nMaster's Degrees\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\nIT Certifications\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\nHEALTH & NURSING\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\nBachelor's Degrees\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\nMaster's Degrees\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\nCertificates\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\nPrevious\\n\\n\\n\\nNext\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\nRecommended Articles\\n\\n\\n\\n\\nTake a look at other articles from WGU. Our articles feature information on a wide variety of subjects, written with the help of subject matter experts and researchers who are well-versed in their industries. This allows us to provide articles with interesting, relevant, and accurate information.\\xa0\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\nThe University\\n\\nAbout Us\\nAccessibility\\nAccreditation\\nNewsroom\\nCareers\\nWGU Store\\n\\n\\n\\n\\nFor Students\\n\\nStudent Portal\\nAdmissions\\nCatalog\\nTitle IX\\nAlumni Services\\nAchievement Wallet\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\nMost Visited Links\\n\\nBusiness Programs\\nBachelor's Degrees\\nStudent Experience\\nOnline Degrees\\nScholarships\\n\\n\\n\\n\\nSupport\\n\\nMilitary\\nScholarships\\nFinancial Aid\\nFaculty\\nTestimonials\\nStudent Communities\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\nPrivacy Policy\\n|\\nCookie Policy\\n|\\nContact Us\\n|\\nSitemap\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n©2026 WGU. All rights reserved.\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\